# Supabase — Data API Security Hardening

> CRITICAL: Supabase's 2025 security retrospective documented mass data breaches caused
> by PostgREST auto-exposing tables with RLS disabled. Run the Security Advisor FIRST.
> Supabase Dashboard → Advisors → Security Advisor → fix every item flagged.

---

## What PostgREST Exposes By Default

Every Supabase project gets an auto-generated REST API (PostgREST) that exposes ALL tables
and views in the `public` schema. Anyone with your anon key can query them.

```
https://[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co/rest/v1/[table_name]
```

**This is not a bug — it is the design.** RLS policies are what control access.
The problem: if RLS is off or policies are wrong, the table is fully public.

---

## Step 1 — Auto-Enable RLS on ALL Tables (run immediately)

```sql
-- Find every table in public schema without RLS enabled
SELECT schemaname, tablename
FROM pg_tables
WHERE schemaname = 'public'
  AND tablename NOT IN (
    SELECT relname FROM pg_class
    WHERE relrowsecurity = true AND relnamespace = 'public'::regnamespace
  );

-- Enable RLS on all of them at once
DO $$
DECLARE
  t RECORD;
BEGIN
  FOR t IN SELECT tablename FROM pg_tables WHERE schemaname = 'public' LOOP
    EXECUTE format('ALTER TABLE public.%I ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY', t.tablename);
    EXECUTE format('ALTER TABLE public.%I FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY', t.tablename);
  END LOOP;
END;
$$;
```

**FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY** — makes RLS apply even to the table owner (postgres role).
Without this, the postgres role (used by migrations and direct connections) bypasses RLS silently.

---

## Step 2 — Event Trigger: Auto-Enable RLS on New Tables

This trigger fires every time a new table is created — ensures no table is ever created without RLS.

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION auto_enable_rls()
RETURNS event_trigger LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$
DECLARE
  obj RECORD;
BEGIN
  FOR obj IN SELECT * FROM pg_event_trigger_ddl_commands()
    WHERE command_tag = 'CREATE TABLE' AND schema_name = 'public'
  LOOP
    EXECUTE format('ALTER TABLE %s ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY', obj.object_identity);
    EXECUTE format('ALTER TABLE %s FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY', obj.object_identity);
  END LOOP;
END;
$$;

CREATE EVENT TRIGGER enforce_rls_on_create
  ON ddl_command_end
  WHEN TAG IN ('CREATE TABLE')
  EXECUTE FUNCTION auto_enable_rls();
```

