## ⚠️ RLS Enabled + No Policies = Silent Empty Results

This is the most confusing Rocket bug: "my data disappeared after I enabled RLS."

```
When RLS is enabled on a table BUT no policies exist:
  - supabase-js returns { data: [], error: null }
  - NO error, NO 403, NO permission denied
  - Data appears to have vanished — queries just return empty

This is intentional PostgreSQL behavior: default-deny means no rows pass.
```

```sql
-- Find tables with RLS enabled but ZERO policies (default-deny = nothing returns)
SELECT c.relname AS table_name
FROM pg_class c
WHERE c.relrowsecurity = true
  AND c.relnamespace = 'public'::regnamespace
  AND NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM pg_policies p
    WHERE p.tablename = c.relname AND p.schemaname = 'public'
  );
-- If this returns rows: add policies OR disable RLS until policies are ready
-- An empty result here = every table with RLS also has at least one policy ✅
```

