## RLS Default Behavior — Dashboard vs SQL vs Migrations

```
Dashboard table creation (2025):
  ✅ RLS is ENABLED by default when creating tables via Table Editor
  ✅ But: no policies are created — table is inaccessible until you add policies

SQL Editor / migrations:
  ❌ RLS is NOT enabled by default
  ❌ You must run: ALTER TABLE tablename ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

External tools (Prisma migrations, Drizzle push, psql):
  ❌ RLS is NOT enabled by default
  ❌ The auto-RLS event trigger (Step 2 above) handles this automatically

Rule: always use the event trigger (Step 2) AND run the bulk enable (Step 1)
      so that ALL tables regardless of how they were created have RLS.
```

