## Step 5 — Move Sensitive Tables to Private Schema (Optional — Maximum Security)

For tables that should NEVER be accessible via the REST API:

```sql
-- Create a private schema (PostgREST only exposes schemas explicitly listed)
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS private;

-- Move table to private schema
ALTER TABLE public.api_keys SET SCHEMA private;
ALTER TABLE public.webhook_secrets SET SCHEMA private;

-- These tables now have NO REST API endpoint whatsoever
-- Access them only from server-side code with service_role or from DB functions
```

```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → Exposed schemas
Default: public
Only schemas listed here are exposed via PostgREST
Remove 'public' and add a clean 'api' schema for complete control (advanced)
```

