## Custom Schema API Access — Fixing PGRST106

When you add a custom schema to "Exposed schemas" in Dashboard but still get PGRST106:

```sql
-- The Dashboard setting alone is sometimes not enough.
-- Also run this to ensure PostgREST picks up the schema change:
ALTER ROLE authenticator SET pgrst.db_schemas TO 'public,myschema';
NOTIFY pgrst, 'reload config';

-- Verify current setting:
SELECT rolconfig FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname = 'authenticator';
```

### Query a specific schema per-request
```typescript
// Switch schema for a single query (supabase-js built-in)
const { data } = await supabase
  .schema('myschema')
  .from('internal_table')
  .select('*')

// Or in server-side code:
const { data } = await adminSupabase
  .schema('private')
  .from('sensitive_table')
  .select('*')
```

