## GraphQL API — Disabled by Default on New Projects (2025)

```
Projects created after 2025: pg_graphql is DISABLED by default.
If your Rocket project uses a GraphQL client and hits 404 → enable it:

Dashboard → Database → Extensions → pg_graphql → toggle ON

Security: if you are NOT using GraphQL, leave it OFF (already the default).
```

```typescript
// GraphQL endpoint (when enabled):
// POST https://[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co/graphql/v1
// Headers:
//   apikey: [your publishable key]           -- always required
//   Authorization: Bearer [user JWT]         -- for authenticated requests
//   Content-Type: application/json

// Basic query:
const response = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL}/graphql/v1`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'apikey': process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
              ?? process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${session.access_token}`,
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    query: `{ ordersCollection(first: 10) { edges { node { id status amountCents } } } }`,
  }),
})
// RLS applies automatically — user only sees their own orders
```

