## New Security Advisor Categories (2025)

Security Advisor now checks these additional categories:

```
1. SECURITY DEFINER functions without SET search_path
   Risk: search_path injection allows privilege escalation
   Fix: always add SET search_path = public to SECURITY DEFINER functions

2. Weak password policy
   Check: Dashboard → Auth → Settings → Password → Minimum length ≥ 8
   Check: Leaked password detection enabled (Pro plan)

3. Extensions with excessive privileges
   Flagged: extensions installed in public schema instead of extensions schema
   Fix: reinstall in extensions schema

4. Leaked API keys
   Supabase scans GitHub for leaked project keys automatically
   You receive an email if a key is found — rotate immediately
```

