## Security Checklist (run before every deploy)

```sql
-- Quick health check — tables without RLS
SELECT tablename
FROM pg_tables t
WHERE schemaname = 'public'
  AND NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM pg_class c
    WHERE c.relname = t.tablename
      AND c.relrowsecurity = true
      AND c.relnamespace = 'public'::regnamespace
  );
-- Should return 0 rows. If any rows: fix immediately.

-- Tables with RLS enabled but NO policies (locked out — nobody can access)
SELECT c.relname AS table_name
FROM pg_class c
WHERE c.relrowsecurity = true
  AND c.relnamespace = 'public'::regnamespace
  AND NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM pg_policies p WHERE p.tablename = c.relname AND p.schemaname = 'public'
  );
-- These tables have RLS but no policies = returns empty for everyone = intentional?
```
